The paper discusses a data analytics engine that prioritizes end-user attention in high-volume fast data streams. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.SE (software engineering), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). The focus on efficient and accurate analyses also suggests a potential fit with cs.PERF (performance). However, given the emphasis on data streams and real-time processing, cs.DB and cs.DS seem like the most likely sub-categories. The use of heavy-hitters sketch and reservoir sampling also suggests a potential fit with cs.DM (data mining).
